'''Don Álvaro''' is a municipality located in the [[Badajoz (province)|province of Badajoz]], [[Extremadura]], [[Spain]]. According to the [[2005]] [[census]] ([[Instituto Nacional de Estadística (Spain)|INE]]), the municipality has a population of 633 inhabitants.

Don Álvaro (Tarfe) is the name of the principle characters in another version of the second book of [[Don Quixote]] published by [[Alonso Fernández de Avellaneda]] in [[Tarragona]] in [[1614]].<ref>Don Quixote by Miguel Cervantes Saavedra, Translated by Walter Starkie (1964), '''page 525''', note 1 ISBN 0-451-52786-0</ref> <ref>Don Quixote by Miguel Cervantes Saavedra, Translated by Walter Starkie (1964), '''page 1034''', note 1 ISBN 0-451-52786-0.</ref> 


